{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A) if {\i f}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?({\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i B}),\u8198?{\i f} injective (resp. surjective), then \u8704?{\i Z}\u8196?\u8838?\u8196?{\i B},\u8198?{\i f\u770?}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?(({\i f}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?1}({\i Z})\u8196?\u8838?\u8196?{\i A})\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i Z}),\u8198?{\i f\u770?}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i f}|{\sub {\i f}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?1}({\i Z})}, the restriction of the function to the corresponding smaller codomain, is also an injection (resp. surjection).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 B) if {\i f}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?({\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i B}),\u8198?{\i f} injective (resp. surjective), then \u8704?{\i Z}\u8196?\u8839?\u8196?{\i B},\u8198?{\i f\u770?}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?({\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i Z}),\u8198?{\i f\u770?}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u953?}\u8197?\u8728?\u8197?{\i f} (with the {\i \u953?} the canonical injection of {\i b}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?{\i B} into its superset {\i Z}), is also an injection (resp. is never a surjection).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 C) if {\i f}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?({\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i B}),\u8198?{\i f} injective, then \u8704?{\i Z}\u8196?\u8838?\u8196?{\i A},\u8198?{\i f\u770?}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?({\i Z}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i B}),\u8198?{\i f}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u953?}{\sub ({\i Z}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i A})}\u8197?\u8728?\u8197?{\i f\u770?}, we have that {\i f\u770?} is also an injection. However, one can construct {\i Z}\u8196?\u8838?\u8196?{\i A} such that {\i f} stops being a surjection.\par}
